#Introduction
JarvisAI is a desktop AI assistant I built using Python and Tkinter.
  It features voice interaction, speech synthesis, weather updates, system monitoring, note-taking and customizable interface.
   #System Requirements
    Windows 10 or newer
    Microphone (For voice commands)
    Internet connection (A stable one if required)
    #Installation Guide
    Click the link provided to enter the download page.
    Click the download button to get the Jarvis_Setup.exe.
    Begin the installation process to install the app.
    If there is security issues ,temporarily turn of your Defender app until after installation.
    Launch JarvisAI.
    #Features
    Speak button: Receives user speech commands / input.
      Send Button: Sends text input to Jarivs.
        Voice Assistant: Allows user interaction with the system using spoken commands.
          Chat Interface: A GUI that enables text-based communication between the user and system.
          Wake-Word Detection: A listening mechanism that continuously monitors audio input for a specific word (like "Jarvis").
            #Troubleshooting
            No voice input- Check microphone permissions.
            App won't start - Run as administrator.
            Speech not working- Verify internet connection.
